#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
nginx-autoblock — behavioral subnet autoblocker for Nginx.

Detects bot crawlers by composite scoring across multiple signals
(UA diversity, request patterns, IP reputation) and adds offending
subnets to nginx's blocklist with TTL.

Designed for CDN-fronted sites (Cloudflare et al.) — does NOT use
static-asset ratio as a signal because CDN edge-caches static
content, making this signal useless at origin.

Usage:
    autoblock                    # production run (intended for cron)
    autoblock --dry-run          # report candidates without writing
    autoblock --show-scores      # diagnostic: top-30 subnets with scores
    autoblock --cleanup          # remove expired auto-bans
    autoblock --config PATH      # alternative config file

Default config path: /etc/nginx-autoblock/config.env
"""

